  "explanation": "In a BST, the LCA is the first node whose value is between p and q. If both p, q < node, move left. If both p, q > node, move right.",
  "answer": "def lowestCommonAncestor(root, p, q):\n    while root:\n        if p < root.val and q < root.val: root = root.left\n        elif p > root.val and q > root.val: root = root.right\n        else: return root",
